SIMPLE: ftp
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ftp
<hw>ftp</hw>,

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: FTP
<hw>FTP</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧f`t⟦emac⟧*p⟦emac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[acronym from
<ets>F</ets>ile <ets>T</ets>ransfer <ets>P</ets>rotocol.]</ety>
<fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>An acronym for <altname>file transfer
protocol</altname>, a standardized protocol used to allow transmission
of files between computers; <as>as, send me the file by
<ex>ftp</ex></as>. It consists of a set of coded signals which are
transmitted between computers, and which inform the receiving computer
of the nature of a packet of information to be transmitted, and inform
the transmitting computer when a packet has been successfully
received.</def> <mark>[acronym]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>FTP</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>ftp</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: ftp
<hw>ftp</hw>,

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: FTP
<hw>FTP</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧f`t⟦emac⟧*p⟦emac⟧")</pr>, <pos>prop. v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>ftp'd</conjf> <it>or</it>
<conjf>FTP'd</conjf> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧f`t⟦emac⟧*p⟦emac⟧d")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>FTPing</conjf> <it>or</it> <conjf>ftp'ing</conjf>
<it>or</it> <conjf>ftp-ing</conjf>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧f`t⟦emac⟧*p⟦emac⟧"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[acronym from
<ets>F</ets>ile <ets>T</ets>ransfer <ets>P</ets>rotocol.]</ety>
<fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>To send from one computer to another by
means of the standard file transfer protocol (ftp); <as>as, he
<ex>ftp'd</ex> me the file yesterday</as>.</def> <mark>[acronym]</mark>
<note>The participle forms have not been standardized, and either
lower-case or upper-case may be used, but when lower-case is used,
either a hyphen or apostrophe is used before the <it>ed</it> or
<it>ing</it> endings.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fu</ent>⟦br⟧
